Goal: Investigate how users discover and save shopping ideas on Pinterest and similar platforms, and identify barriers to purchase decision-making.

Methods:
	•	Survey 100+ users about their experience using Pinterest for shopping inspiration.
	•	Conduct 5 usability tests to observe how users browse, save, and act on shopping-related content.
	•	Analyze engagement data to determine how saved items influence future purchase decisions.

Deliverables:
	•	A research study summarizing insights on how users transition from inspiration to purchase.
	•	User journey map illustrating decision-making pain points and opportunities for enhancing shopping interactions on Pinterest.
	•	Suggested product improvements to make saved shopping ideas more actionable for users.
